📖We, same as many other businesses, do have “deposit and cancellation policy” - 𝐰𝐡𝐢𝐜𝐡 𝐢𝐬 𝐛𝐞𝐢𝐧𝐠 𝐫𝐞𝐚𝐝 𝐚𝐧𝐝 𝐬𝐢𝐠𝐧𝐞𝐝 𝐛𝐲 𝐚𝐥𝐥 𝐨𝐮𝐫 𝐜𝐥𝐢𝐞𝐧𝐭𝐬 as part of our agreement. Complete text is also available on our website for public notice and we are always here to help if you have any questions.

🙅‍♂️The policy exists NOT as a punishment for being inconsistent or disrespectful or else… All our clients are adults who are able take responsibility for their own actions and decisions. 

🙇‍♂️The reason behind this policy is very simple - survivability of business. 
As many of you know we work with one client per day and George is the only artist at the studio. 
Therefore every last moment cancellation is damaging for our business.

🧘This model was adopted in 2020 when we decided to prioritize privacy and tranquility of the space, which we believe most of our clients can appreciate - being tattooed in this atmosphere is much more productive and comforting rather than being surrounded by other tattooists and their clients. 
Thank you we truly appreciate those who … appreciate 🙏😊

Up ⬆️ up ⬆️ up ⬆️ 
True warriors those who set up their goals and achieve them. Step by step.

Takigyo. Waterfall meditation is a rare practice that samurai and ascetic Japanese Buddhists and Shintoists engaged in for centuries. Whether translated as waterfall meditation or training, it is a shocking, exhilarating, and memorable introduction to an extraordinary form of spiritual development and self-control (full article - allabout-japan.com)

Painful, shocking, physically and mentally challenging conditions one put himself(herself) voluntarily. In order to stay present and awake, purified if you will. 

Doesn’t it remind you tattooing? 
STAY PRESENT guys, concentrate on the pain, let it help you to be in the moment, feel it in order to achieve spiritual growth. Learn to be comfortable in discomfort. 
 
Sadly, most people would prefer to hide in their phones.
_________________

Kunichika: Ichikawa Sadanji Beneath a Waterfall.

“Creativity takes courage.” Henri Matisse. 
What if a canvas is your body and inks stay for life- that’s courage indeed.

Pair of six-panel screens; Ink, color, gold pigment and silver leaf on paper. 
Skeletons depicted meditating or playing or even tattooing(?) … at least it seems like tattooing….
Also we were surprised to see very famous #kyosai among other beautiful pieces 🤍

Second sleeve for  @dannyfatcat - skeleton and snake full sleeve.
I wanted to mention, that even though full sleeve usually takes about 8 sessions, sometimes, like in this case, it takes longer, due to various factors such as: 1. Skin sensitivity - ginger type of skin is super sensitive and freckles aren’t helping. 
2. Design details. 
3. Healing. 
4. Overall size and Chest plate size. 
It took 12 sessions for Danny. Which makes it even more challenging 💪💪💪
